NOTICE — precompute/vendor/gigs/
================================

This directory vendors a small, single-license subset of GI-GS.

Upstream project
----------------
GI-GS: Global Illumination Decomposition on Gaussian Splatting for Inverse
Rendering (ICLR 2025), arXiv:2410.02619.
Source: https://github.com/stopaimme/GI-GS
License: MIT — "Copyright (c) 2024 stopaimme" (see the LICENSE file here,
copied verbatim from the upstream repository root).

What is vendored (verbatim)
---------------------------
* LICENSE            — verbatim copy of the upstream MIT LICENSE.
* pbr_math.py        — an EXACT extraction of 8 import-free helper functions from
                       upstream `pbr/shade.py` (retyped one at a time, NOT copied
                       wholesale then trimmed). These carry no restricted imports:
                         - envBRDF_approx   (Lazarov 2013 analytic env-BRDF; this
                                             replaces the restricted NVIDIA
                                             brdf_256_256.bin split-sum LUT)
                         - saturate_dot
                         - aces_film        (ACES tone map)
                         - linear_to_srgb
                         - _rgb_to_srgb / rgb_to_srgb
                         - _srgb_to_rgb / srgb_to_rgb

That is the COMPLETE vendorable set.

What is NOT vendored — reimplemented FRESH elsewhere (authored, never lifted)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
The following capabilities the decompose port needs are reimplemented from the
paper / from scratch in the main tree (precompute/stages/decompose.py and
precompute/core/sh_env.py), NOT copied from GI-GS — several upstream source files
carry pasted Inria/GRAPHDECO headers despite the MIT repo, so they are
reference-only:
  * pbr_shading_sh          — deferred SH split-sum shading (GI-GS's pbr_shading
                              is a cubemap / nvdiffrast `dr.texture` path; ours is
                              a pure-torch degree-2 SH environment). Reuses the
                              vendored envBRDF_approx.
  * SHEnvLight              — degree-2 SH environment light (GI-GS uses a learnable
                              HDR cubemap `CubemapLight` + nvdiffrec prefilters).
  * material parameterization + activations, depth->normal, the L1/SSIM/TV losses,
    the exponential LR schedule, and all SH basis / cosine-lobe (A_l) / coordinate
    -flip constants.

What is NEVER vendored (license walls — must not enter this repo in any form)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  * submodules/diff-gaussian-rasterization/**  (Inria/GRAPHDECO non-commercial
                                                fork; the G-buffer + screen-space
                                                indirect CUDA kernels)
  * submodules/nvdiffrast/**                    (NVIDIA Source Code License)
  * submodules/simple-knn/**
  * pbr/renderutils/**, pbr/brdf_256_256.bin    (NVIDIA nvdiffrec, all rights reserved)
  * utils/sh_utils.py                           (PlenOctree BSD-2 — a 3rd license
                                                family; SH constants are authored
                                                fresh to keep this tree single-license)
  * any build/lib.linux-*/ byte-duplicate of the above.
